  "text": "analysis detected the specific Mfge8 bands in normal arteries ( Figure 1A ). Interestingly, we found a lower expression of Mfge8 in advanced atherosclerotic vessels ( Figure 1A ). We obtained similar results in mice (Data Supplement Figure I ). Using immunohistochemistry, we found that Mfge8 was expressed in endothelial cells, smooth muscle cells, and plaque macrophages, beginning from the early stages of lesion development ( Figure 1B  through 1I) ; however, the intensity of Mfge8 staining was lower in macrophages located in the cholesterol-rich lipid core of advanced plaques, where apoptotic debris accumulates ( Figure 1B and 1C and Data Supplement Figure  II) . [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] This is in agreement with a recent finding showing a downregulation of Mfge8 mRNA expression in a subset of free cholesterol-loaded macrophages. [CITATION_3] In addition, apoptotic cell death as detected by TUNEL staining occurred more frequently in areas with low Mfge8 expression in advanced human lesions (Data Supplement Figure  III ).",
